            "content": "The stability programme for mAb-X follows ICH Q5C (Quality of Biotechnological Products: Stability Testing) with the following design: Long-term: 2-8C (target storage), tested at 0, 3, 6, 9, 12, 18, 24, 36 months using the full stability panel (SEC, CE-SDS, iCIEF, HILIC-FLR, potency, peptide mapping [selected timepoints], pH, appearance, subvisible particles). Accelerated: 25C/60% RH, tested at 0, 1, 3, 6 months — this condition accelerates deamidation, aggregation, and fragmentation and confirms the degradation pathways identified during forced degradation. Stress: 40C/75% RH, tested at 0, 2 weeks, 1 month — demonstrates the molecule is sufficiently stable to survive temperature excursions during shipping and handling. Photostability: ICH Q1B Option 2 (1.2M lux-hours visible + 200 W-hr/m2 UV-A) — demonstrates packaging protects against light-induced Trp oxidation and aggregation. In-use: simulate clinical preparation (dilution in 0.9% NaCl infusion bag, stored at room temperature for 24 hours) — confirms stability under in-use conditions. Three batches minimum at each condition (PPQ batches for initial filing, annual stability batches for ongoing verification). The stability data support the 24-month shelf life claim and provide the trending data for the continuous process verification programme."
